<subSubSection pageId="3" pageNumber="66" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="3.[151,1437,792,2005]" pageId="3" pageNumber="66">
<emphasis box="[151,377,793,817]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="66">Female macroptera</emphasis>
. Body including antennae yellowish brown, pronotum and terminal abdominal segments lighter, fore wing shaded; major setae on head, pronotum and tergites yellow. With character states in the generic diagnosis. Head with transverse reticulation behind eyes, ocellar region with little or no sculpture; ocellar setae III at least twice as long as ocellar setae I and II. Pronotum with transverse lines of sculpture. Fore wing first vein with about 
<number box="[220,234,936,960]" pageId="3" pageNumber="66" value="9.0">9</number>
setae on basal half and 
<number box="[504,518,936,960]" pageId="3" pageNumber="66" value="3.0">3</number>
setae distributed along distal half; second vein with about 
<number box="[1180,1208,936,960]" pageId="3" pageNumber="66" value="12.0">12</number>
setae; clavus with 
<number box="[1422,1436,936,960]" pageId="3" pageNumber="66" value="4.0">4</number>
veinal setae and 
<number box="[349,363,972,996]" pageId="3" pageNumber="66" value="1.0">1</number>
discal seta. Abdominal tergites II–VII with weak sculpture medially, VIII without comb of microtrichia, IX median dorsal setae not extending to posterior margin and situated laterally.
</paragraph>
